                    <h5 class="card-title mb-4">Important Information About Blood Donation</h5>

                    <h6 class="mb-3">Donation Amount</h6>
                    <p>A standard whole blood donation is approximately 450-500 milliliters (about one pint). This
                        amount is carefully chosen as it's safe for most donors while being enough to help save lives.
                    </p>

                    <h6 class="mb-3">Waiting Period</h6>
                    <p>You must wait at least 8 weeks (56 days) between whole blood donations. This waiting period is
                        essential because:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>It takes about 4-6 weeks for your body to completely replenish the red blood cells lost
                            during donation</li>
                        <li>This ensures your iron levels return to normal</li>
                        <li>It helps prevent iron deficiency and maintains your health</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h6 class="mb-3">Eligibility</h6>
                    <p>To be eligible for donation, you must:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Wait the full 8-week period between donations</li>
                        <li>Match the blood type requirements for the specific request</li>
                        <li>Be in good health on the day of donation</li>
                    </ul>

                    <div class="alert alert-danger mt-4">
                        <i class="fas fa-exclamation-circle me-2"></i>
                        Your blood type information cannot be changed after registration. Please ensure it was entered
                        correctly.
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
